abstract: Accusations of an assassination attempt on Vladimir Putin.
snippet: Accusations of an assassination attempt on Vladimir Putin.
lead_paragraph: After a pair of explosions above the Kremlin early yesterday, Russia accused Ukraine of trying to assassinate Vladimir Putin, the Russian leader, with a drone attack. Kyiv denied any involvement and asserted that Russia had manufactured the incident to distract attention from Ukraine’s expected imminent counteroffensive and possibly to justify an escalation of its own attacks.

abstract: Investigators have uncovered widespread evidence of abuse by Moscow’s forces, including rape and forced nudity. Kremlin officials have repeatedly denied accusations of rights violations.
snippet: Investigators have uncovered widespread evidence of abuse by Moscow’s forces, including rape and forced nudity. Kremlin officials have repeatedly denied accusations of rights violations.
lead_paragraph: KHERSON, Ukraine — On her eighth or ninth day in Russian detention, Olha, a 26-year-old Ukrainian, was tied to a table, naked to the waist. For 15 minutes, her interrogator leveled obscenities at her, then threw a jacket over her and let seven other men into the room.

main: ‘Fear Still Remains’: Ukraine Finds Sexual Crimes Where Russian Troops Ruled
print_headline: Ukraine Finds Evidence of Sex Crimes in Areas Russia Occupied

abstract: The Saudi crown prince is seeking a civilian nuclear program and security assurances from President Biden, a steep price for an agreement long sought by Israel.
snippet: The Saudi crown prince is seeking a civilian nuclear program and security assurances from President Biden, a steep price for an agreement long sought by Israel.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Saudi Arabia is seeking security guarantees from the United States, help with developing a civilian nuclear program and fewer restrictions on U.S. arms sales as its price for normalizing relations with Israel, people familiar with the exchanges say.

main: Saudi Arabia Offers Its Price to Normalize Relations With Israel
print_headline: Saudi Arabia Offers A Price to Normalize  Relations With Israel

snippet: Long seen as a regional troublemaker and on the defensive from advances made by Israel, Iran sees the restoration of ties with its rival as a win for all sides, analysts say.
lead_paragraph: For years, Iran’s standing as a Mideast power has been battered on a number of fronts.

abstract: The authorities detained a woman they said had delivered the bomb, hidden in a statuette, that killed the blogger, and called it the work of antigovernment activists and Ukraine.
snippet: The authorities detained a woman they said had delivered the bomb, hidden in a statuette, that killed the blogger, and called it the work of antigovernment activists and Ukraine.
lead_paragraph: The Russian authorities on Monday detained a suspect in the bombing that killed a popular pro-war blogger in the center of St. Petersburg, and blamed Ukraine and Russian opposition activists for the attack, signaling that the Kremlin could use the explosion to escalate its harsh crackdown against what remains of antiwar activism in Russia.

main: Russia Accuses Dissidents and Ukraine of Killing Pro-War Blogger
print_headline: Russia Detains a Suspect in a Killing, and Shifts the Blame to Ukraine

abstract: In a hearing at Guantánamo Bay, an expert gave a graphic public depiction of torture after the Sept. 11, 2001, terror attacks.
snippet: In a hearing at Guantánamo Bay, an expert gave a graphic public depiction of torture after the Sept. 11, 2001, terror attacks.
lead_paragraph: GUANTÁNAMO BAY, Cuba — Over the years, the Central Intelligence Agency’s use of waterboarding and other forms of torture in its secret overseas prisons after the Sept. 11, 2001, attacks has been revealed in government leaks, testimony and a damning Senate investigation.

main: Doctor Describes and Denounces C.I.A. Practice of ‘Rectal Feeding’ of Prisoners
print_headline: Doctor Denounces the C.I.A.’s ‘Rectal Feeding’ of Prisoners

abstract: The company’s grip on ticket sales, and its move last year to cancel sales for Taylor Swift’s upcoming tour, will be a big focus of an antitrust-focused hearing.
snippet: The company’s grip on ticket sales, and its move last year to cancel sales for Taylor Swift’s upcoming tour, will be a big focus of an antitrust-focused hearing.
lead_paragraph: Two months after Ticketmaster canceled sales for Taylor Swift’s upcoming Eras tour, a top executive from its parent company, Live Nation Entertainment, will appear at the Senate on Tuesday to defend the company. (Ms. Swift herself is not scheduled to show up.)

main: Live Nation Faces a Skeptical Senate

original: By Andrew Ross Sorkin, Ravi Mattu, Bernhard Warner, Sarah Kessler, Michael J. de la Merced, Lauren Hirsch and Ephrat Livni

abstract: For half a century, Geoffrey Hinton nurtured the technology at the heart of chatbots like ChatGPT. Now he worries it will cause serious harm.
snippet: For half a century, Geoffrey Hinton nurtured the technology at the heart of chatbots like ChatGPT. Now he worries it will cause serious harm.
lead_paragraph: Geoffrey Hinton was an artificial intelligence pioneer. In 2012, Dr. Hinton and two of his graduate students at the University of Toronto created technology that became the intellectual foundation for the A.I. systems that the tech industry’s biggest companies believe is a key to their future.

main: ‘The Godfather of A.I.’ Leaves Google and Warns of Danger Ahead
print_headline: He Warns of Risks From A.I. He Helped Create

abstract: State-backed demonstrations to mark the 1979 event, a touchstone of the Iranian Revolution, were widely broadcast on TV and come as anti-government protests have rocked the country.
snippet: State-backed demonstrations to mark the 1979 event, a touchstone of the Iranian Revolution, were widely broadcast on TV and come as anti-government protests have rocked the country.
lead_paragraph: Iran on Friday marked the anniversary of the 1979 takeover of the U.S. embassy in Tehran with a flurry of state-backed demonstrations that stood in stark contrast to the anti-government protests that have engulfed the country and posed one of the biggest challenges to its ruling clerics.

main: As Protests Rage, Iran Marks Anniversary of U.S. Embassy Takeover
print_headline: As Protests Rage, Iran Marks 1979 U.S. Embassy Takeover
